      "author": "Esmaeelpour",
      "description": "### New\n\n- **Task autocomplete** — start typing in a checkbox and DoneZone suggests matching tasks from anywhere in the note (done or not). Selecting a suggestion moves that task onto the line you're typing and removes the original, collapsing duplicates into one entry. The task adopts the state of the line you're typing into:\n  - Typing in an **unchecked** box → an archived (checked) task comes back active.\n  - Typing in a **checked** box → an open task is marked done.\n\n  Toggle it under **Settings → DoneZone → Task autocomplete** (on by default).",
      "downloadCount": 1,
